quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  20,111,"And all faces will be humbled before the Ever-Living, All-Sustaining. And those burdened with wrongdoing will be in loss"
  20,112,But whoever does good and is a believer will have no fear of being wronged or denied ňĻtheir rewardňļ
  20,113,"And so We have sent it down as an Arabic Quran and varied the warnings in it, so perhaps they will shun evil or it may cause them to be mindful"
  20,114,"Exalted is Allah, the True King! Do not rush to recite ňĻa revelation ofňļ the Quran ňĻO Prophetňļ before it is ňĻproperlyňļ conveyed to you,¬†and pray, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Increase me in knowledge.‚ÄĚ"
  20,115,"And indeed, We once made a covenant with Adam, but he forgot, and ňĻsoňļ We did not find determination in him"
  20,116,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We said to the angels, ‚ÄúProstrate before Adam,‚ÄĚ so they all did‚ÄĒbut not Ibl√ģs,¬†who refused ňĻarrogantlyňļ"
  20,117,"So We cautioned, ‚ÄúO Adam! This is surely an enemy to you and to your wife. So do not let him drive you both out of Paradise, for you ňĻO Adamňļ would then suffer ňĻhardshipňļ"
  20,118,Here it is guaranteed that you will never go hungry or unclothed
  20,119,nor will you ňĻeverňļ suffer from thirst or ňĻthe sun‚Äôsňļ heat.‚ÄĚ
  20,120,"But Satan whispered to him, saying, ‚ÄúO Adam! Shall I show you the Tree of Immortality and a kingdom that does not fade away?‚ÄĚ"
  20,121,"So they both ate from the tree and then their nakedness was exposed to them, prompting them to cover themselves with leaves from Paradise. So Adam disobeyed his Lord, and ňĻsoňļ lost his way"
  20,122,"Then his Lord chose him ňĻfor His graceňļ, accepted his repentance, and guided him ňĻrightlyňļ"
  20,123,"Allah said, ‚ÄúDescend, both of you, from here together ňĻwith Satanňļ as enemies to each other. Then when guidance comes to you from Me, whoever follows My guidance will neither go astray ňĻin this lifeňļ nor suffer ňĻin the nextňļ"
  20,124,"But whoever turns away from My Reminder will certainly have a miserable life,¬†then We will raise them up blind on the Day of Judgment.‚ÄĚ"
  20,125,"They will cry, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Why have you raised me up blind, although I used to see?‚ÄĚ"
  20,126,"Allah will respond, ‚ÄúIt is so, just as Our revelations came to you and you neglected them, so Today you are neglected.‚ÄĚ"
  20,127,This is how We reward whoever transgresses and does not believe in the revelations of their Lord. And the punishment of the Hereafter is far more severe and more lasting
  20,128,"Is it not yet clear to them how many peoples We destroyed before them, whose ruins they still pass by? Surely in this are signs for people of sound judgment"
  20,129,"Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord¬†ňĻO Prophetňļ and a term already set, their ňĻinstantňļ doom would have been inevitable"
  20,130,"So be patient ňĻO Prophetňļ with what they say. And glorify the praises of your Lord before sunrise and before sunset, and glorify Him in the hours of the night and at both ends of the day,¬†so that you may be pleased ňĻwith the rewardňļ"
  20,131,"Do not let your eyes crave what We have allowed some of the disbelievers to enjoy; the ňĻfleetingňļ splendour of this worldly life, which We test them with. But your Lord‚Äôs provision ňĻin the Hereafterňļ is far better and more lasting"
  20,132,"Bid your people to pray, and be diligent in ňĻobservingňļ it. We do not ask you to provide. It is We Who provide for you. And the ultimate outcome is ňĻonlyňļ for ňĻthe people ofňļ righteousness"
  20,133,"They demand, ‚ÄúIf only he could bring us a sign from his Lord!‚ÄĚ¬†Have they not ňĻalreadyňļ received a confirmation of what is in earlier Scriptures"
  20,134,"Had We destroyed them with a torment before this ňĻProphet cameňļ, they would have surely argued, ‚ÄúOur Lord! If only You had sent us a messenger, we would have followed Your revelations before being humiliated and put to shame.‚ÄĚ"
  20,135,"Say ňĻto them, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúEach ňĻof usňļ is waiting, so keep waiting! You will soon know who is on the Straight Path and is ňĻrightlyňļ guided.‚ÄĚ"